User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US) AppleWebKit/534.16 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/10.0.628.0 Safari/534.16
Build Identifier: 

If you go here:

http://closure-library.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/closure/goog/demos/button.html

Type fb1 in the console it says "goog.ui.Button" instead of "Object" in Chrome (thanks to support from V8). Smarter naming would be a huge plus for Firebug, etc. Debugging a bunch of unnamed functions is a mess in complex toolkits and frameworks like YUI, ExtJS, Dojo, etc.

Also filed as a Firebug issue: http://code.google.com/p/fbug/issues/detail?id=3844



Reproducible: Always
